---
title: Bok Choy and Black Rice Veggie Bowl with Marinated Radishes and Mushrooms
description: Black rice, like blueberries and eggplant, gets its stunning deep color from anthocyanins,  natural pigments that are also heart-healthy antioxidants. That’s not the only reason to eat it up, however—it has a delightfully nutty, earthy flavor and sturdy al dente texture. That flavor and heft make it the perfect medium for soaking up the soy and sesame-accented sauce in this recipe’s bok choy and mushroom stir-fry.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w11-r9-2e48a3bc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w11-r9-0e2d8ffc.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 500 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 2.5 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 12 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 620 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bok-choy-and-black-rice-veggie-bowl-58920a407d69bf763576f6b2
author: HelloFresh
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to boil. Add @Black Thai Rice{3/4%cup} and boil until
tender, about ~{30%minutes}. Drain and set aside until meal is ready.

> No need to measure out the water—you're cooking the rice like pasta here.

Wash and dry all produce. Separate tender leaves from crisp stems of
@Baby Bok Choy{2}. Thinly slice the stems. Peel @Ginger{1%thumb}, then finely mince
until you have ½ TBSP. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}. Thinly slice @Radishes{3}.
Trim @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}, then thinly slice.

Toss radishes in a small #bowl{} with @White Wine Vinegar{2%tablespoon} and a pinch
of @salt{}. Set aside to marinate.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add garlic and ginger. Cook, tossing, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add
mushrooms and cook, tossing, until softened and a few shades darker in color,
about ~{5%minutes}.

Add bok choy stems to pan and cook until tender but still crisp, about ~{3%minutes}.
Add bok choy leaves, @Soy Sauce{1%ounce}, and @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon}. Toss to
coat veggies. Cook until bok choy leaves are just wilted and sesame oil is
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with mushroom and bok choy mixture. Garnish
with radishes and @Cashew Pieces{1%ounce}.